Howdy folks! I stumbled upon a problem that leaves me really confused.
I am building a custom 404 page and I am pre-loading 3 modules inside: a nav, a hero and a footer.

```
{% custom_widget "SR Navbar Dropdown 01" widget_name='SR Navbar Dropdown 01' %}
{% custom_widget "SR Hero 404" widget_name='SR Hero 404' %}
{% custom_widget "SR Footer 01" widget_name='SR Footer 01' %}
```

Problem is that the navbar and the footer are rendered, but the hero is not. Instead the page has this error message:

```
&lt;span id="hs_cos_wrapper_SR_Hero_404" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_custom_widget" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="widget" data-hs-cos-type="custom_widget"&gt;
  &lt;!-- custom widget definition not found --&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;
```

I've been turning this on all sides for hours and I can't understand why things are happening like that.

Thanks for the time.
